President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Richard J. Engler as a member of the Chemical Safety and Hazard Investigation Board and Linda A. Puchala as a member of the National Mediation Board. Engler is the Founder and Director of the New Jersey Work Environment Council and has a background in occupational safety and health. Puchala currently serves as a member of the National Mediation Board and has experience in alternative dispute resolution and labor relations. Both nominees bring expertise and talent to their new roles in the Administration.